      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "COSTA STAR (5) has placed three of last four, the latest led and was nabbed late here when runner-up. That was behind Violet and from that same race finished in front of a coupe of chances in the first today and a couple of chances in this. Looks hard to beat, especially if that form has been franked earlier. RIVER BEAUTY (8) was yet another from the Violet race. Has ability and rates one of the better chances. REINCARNATED (3) was well in the market at York on debut and gave a sight, finishing a fair fifth after trying to lead throughout. Blinkers added and will be in this for a long way. WILD GOSSIP (10) placed fresh then was another to come through the Violet race, finishing fifth. Can do much better. DASHING DIVA (9) was safely held in the Violet race but was gassed early from the wide draw. Much better gate this time so can improve.",
